ACTRESS Letoya Makhene’s Facebook page has been hacked. The news was announced by Letoya on Sunday morning, 2 January. She said the hacker is sending porn through her account. She has asked her followers to help her report this matter. According to her post, the last time she used her Facebook page was on Friday. In her Instagram post, she wrote: “My Facebook page has been hacked!!! My page has been hacked. I last posted on Friday and I woke up to find that I no longer have control of my page and that my team and I have been removed. They’re posting porn and I need your assistance to report this to FB.” ALSO READ |DUMI MKOKSTAD IS PROUD OF JUMBO Fortunately her followers already suspected that the account was no longer controlled by her. Lesedi Kgono posted: “Thokoza, Gogo. This has been happening to most of us. If you couldn’t report it, I will because I had the same problem. I saw a post of a video which they use to hack other people.” Phemelo said: “I thought as much because when I saw those posts, I thought this can’t be you.” On Thursday, Letoya posted a video clip to assure her followers that this was her page but the following day, the hackers took the page. A post shared by Letoya Makhene-Pulumo (@letoyamakhenep) 